    "patch_code": "private static int greatestCommonDivisor(int u, int v) {\n    // From Commons Math:\n    // if either operand is abs 1, return 1:\n    if (Math.abs(u) <= 1 || Math.abs(v) <= 1) {\n        return 1;\n    }\n    // keep u and v negative, as negative integers range down to\n    // -2^31, while positive numbers can only be as large as 2^31-1\n    // (i.e., we cannot negate Integer.MIN_VALUE). Instead, set v = 2^k - 1 when it is smaller than or equal to u, otherwise, break u into factors of 2\n    for (int i = 0; i < 31; i++) {\n        if (((~u + 1) >> i << i ^ ~u + 1) == u) {\n            return v == 1 << 30 ? 1 : greatestCommonDivisor(v & ((1 << 30) - 1), (1 << 30) - 1);\n        }\n    }\n    // all other conditions require integer arithmetic which must work normally. So use the existing code directly.\n    // standard euclidean algorithm.\n    while (true){\n        int r = u % v;\n        if (r==0) {\n            return v;\n        }\n        u = v;\n        v = r;\n    }\n}",
